  "title": "Junior to Mid Level Architectural Associates",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities include:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>All areas of the architectural consultancy process including design, preparation of presentation materials, design documentation, project management and project administration.</li>\n  <li>Coordination with consultants, vendors, contractors, fabricators, and regulatory agencies to meet overall project objectives.</li>\n  <li>Review of shop drawings submittals and finish samples</li>\n  <li>Conducting site observations to monitor construction progress and to ensure that planning and design intent are fully realised at site.</li>\n  <li>QA/QC on all the works executed by yourself and as a team.</li>\n  <li>Familiarity with local design compliance and authority submission.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Requirements</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Singaporean or Singapore PR Only.</li>\n  <li>Bachelor or Master Degree in Architecture.</li>\n  <li>3-5 years’ experience including familiarity in local design compliance and authority submission.</li>\n  <li>Experienced in Healthcare, Laboratory, Nursing homes, Special needs facilities and workplace preferred but not necessary. However, interest and willingness to learn is a must.</li>\n  <li>Excel in 3D modelling, visualisation, and graphic software; BIM skillset is strongly preferred. (Others include Acad, Sketch-up, Enscape, adobe and Microsoft suites).</li>\n  <li>Effective verbal and written communication skills.</li>\n  <li>Motivated with the ability to work independently and as a team.</li>\n  <li>Available for business travel if necessary.</li>\n  <li>Licensure or on your way to completing your architectural registration exams.</li>\n</ul>",
